Name: Dr. Bo-Laun
Species: Clawitzer
Courses: She's the nurse, but could probably teach health if it became...
body:
Teacher? Introduction

Name: Dr. Bo-Laun

Species: Clawitzer

Courses: She’s the nurse, but could probably teach health if it became necessary.

Personality: (Hasty/Proud of her power) Despite looking relatively intimidating, especially with her cannon arm and somewhat muscular form, she’s quite friendly and energetic. Perhaps she gets a bit TOO excited about helping others, but at least there’s no doubt that she loves her job. Just don’t get on her bad side.

Relationships with other teachers: She acts rather ‘buddy-buddy’ with them, no matter what they think of her. However, she by no means goes out of her way to interact with them, preferring to stay in her office over meetings.

Any other fun stuff: Though Heal Pulse is her most commonly-used move, all her other moves are attacking moves. As they aren’t as common, she uses items to deal with status conditions. Also she’s trans, and proud of it.

((character and art by @walking-in-a-dream ))

summary:
Bastien Sketches ft. A beardless baby Lysandre
Bas is a protective older brother, and he’s far more serious and cynical because...
body:
Bastien Sketches ft. A beardless baby Lysandre

Bas is a protective older brother, and he’s far more serious and cynical because he wants to keep Lysandre happy and himself. He became king rather young because his parents had to spend more time at the league due to the previous champion’s disappearance, and while the title of king didn’t mean huge responsibility, he still felt like it did.

He also swore like a sailor when he was younger, which he was able to tame when he had to take the role of a king more seriously, but it was still a huge part of his personality.

Species: Jumpluff
Courses: Journalism, Public Speaking
Grading Style: Slightly harsh for both...
body:
Teacher Introduction

Name: Professor (Mrs.) Tarax

Species: Jumpluff

Courses: Journalism, Public Speaking

Grading Style: Slightly harsh for both classes. She’ll push people to speak clearly and find good stories to report

Personality: She’s very street-smart and confident in herself, and knows how to get her way through nothing but persuasion.

Relationships with other teachers: Doesn’t get along with Dr. Solveig on account of them making it more difficult to get juicy stories to report. Often encourages students to approach Professor Midgelit for entertaining footage.

Any other fun stuff: She absolutely LOVES gossip, and will listen to and spread gossip from both teachers and students. Will often spend nights watching talkshows while drinking wine and eating chocolates.

((art and character by @sometimes-shiny-lurantis ))

summary: Pokemon Card of the Day #1497: Energy Switch (Black & White)
title: Pokemon Card of the Day #1497: Energy Switch (Black & White)
body: Also returning in the Black & White set was Energy Switch, which simply let you move a basic Energy from 1 of your Pokemon to another. This wasn’t used all that often, but some people liked to toss this in just for a little extra flexibility. Darkrai EX decks, again, were the most natural fit since you could just move over a Darkness Energy to help with retreating if needed. It was never required but could be considered as a safety option if there was room in a deck.
